    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segmentation fault in PUCCH format 2 resource counting function\n\n### Summary\nThe newly implemented `get_nb_pucch2_per_slot` function can cause a segmentation fault when processing UEs with malformed PUCCH configurations. The function dereferences PUCCH resource pointers without checking if they are NULL first.\n\nThis fix adds proper NULL pointer checks before accessing PUCCH resource structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/config.c`: Added NULL checks for PUCCH resource pointers in get_nb_pucch2_per_slot()\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/mac_proto.h`: No changes needed\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a UE with a PUCCH configuration containing NULL resource entries\n2. Trigger PUCCH scheduling for that UE\n3. The gNB will crash with a segmentation fault in get_nb_pucch2_per_slot()\n\nThe crash occurs because the function loops through the PUCCH resource list but doesn't verify each resource pointer is valid before accessing its format field. When a NULL pointer is dereferenced, the process terminates with SIGSEGV.\n\n"
}